Package sample

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Item
    Item interface defines what method needs to be implemented by the classes that use it.
    MultimediaControl
    Interface that forces a class to implement the methods defined.
    ScreenSpec
    Interface that sets what methods need to be included in a class.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AudioPlayer
    Audio player class represents a Product object that can play audio.
    Controller
    This controller class runs the production program and utilizes the many coding practices learned in COP 3003.
    Employee
    Employee class is used to help create employee objects in program that will allow a backlog to be traced back to certain users.
    Main
    Main application that launches the FX program while adding the effects of the css stylesheets.
    MoviePlayer
    Movie Player class that utilizes an interface and super class to create an object that can be a movie player.
    Product
    Product class is a super class that is used to help create product objects in the main function of the program.
    ProductionRecord
    Production Record class is used to create objects of that type in order to produce a log of products.
    Screen
    Screen class that uses Screen Spec interface in order to apply variables to the object.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ItemType
    Enum class that defines products with special data types.
    MonitorType
    Enum that allows objects to have specific screen types if applicable.
